The STACKPROTECTOR hang's load-bearing hardware site is
unidentified after this audit pass. The bug *is* hardware
(STACKPROTECTOR doesn't change kernel logic, only adds
prologue/epilogue cycles, and the same kernel boots without it),
but the specific site is subtle.

Possible deeper investigations:
- Cycle-by-cycle hwsim diff between the two builds (with vs
  without STACKPROTECTOR) at the same kernel time, looking for
  where pipeline state diverges.
- Forced LR/SC-around-IRQ probe at byte level (silicon firmware)
  to test bridge round-trip under the specific timing pattern.
